RESIDENTS CREATE NEW PARK NORTHCOTE AVENUE RECREATION GROUND
----------------------------------------------------------------------

    Residents are hoping to transform the Northcote Avenue Recreation
    Ground, known locally as the 'Pit Park', into a landscaped area and
    nature reserve. Although just within the borough of Hounslow, the
    park faces Richmond across the River Crane, the middle of which
    marks the borough boundary. For this reason it has always been used
    by residents of North St Margarets as well as their Hounslow
    neighbours, being for many their nearest open space.

